61
00:05:40,557 --> 00:05:42,867
- Oh.
- I could come back.

62
00:05:43,026 --> 00:05:46,030
No, no, no. Come on in.

63
00:05:46,196 --> 00:05:48,369
I was just sleeping.

64
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:53,045
I've been walking in the rain.

65
00:05:53,203 --> 00:05:57,310
PIERRE: So, what happened
to your boyfriend, the Canadian guy?

66
00:05:58,208 --> 00:05:59,687
CARRIE: He went back to Canada.

67
00:06:00,911 --> 00:06:02,686
Sorry.

68
00:06:11,388 --> 00:06:13,834
I remember how you used to play.

69
00:06:13,991 --> 00:06:15,971
In high school.

70
00:06:16,827 --> 00:06:19,273
I would listen to you
outside of the music room.

71
00:06:20,097 --> 00:06:23,510
I just had the strangest dream.

72
00:06:23,967 --> 00:06:27,005
CARRIE: Well, one time, I did that.

73
00:06:27,838 --> 00:06:29,340
And I remember thinking...

74
00:06:29,506 --> 00:06:30,780
(STRUMS CELLO)

75
00:06:30,941 --> 00:06:35,856
that the sound of it was so mournful.

76
00:06:36,213 --> 00:06:39,092
And I made fun of myself
for thinking that word.

77
00:06:40,617 --> 00:06:44,622
Because all I meant was that I liked it.

78
00:06:48,859 --> 00:06:50,839
Do you wanna hear my dream?

79
00:06:51,361 --> 00:06:52,965
No.

80
00:06:53,831 --> 00:06:55,833
Did things...

81
00:06:56,433 --> 00:06:58,538
